<p>Continue bringing in some of the â€œwiderâ€ bits of DWP into the designing as well. Some of that happened this week, but itâ€™s a good time to layer some complexities in.</p>

<p>Do some prototype work on a bit of the service, probably a calculating tool. Itâ€™ll allow Sam to focus on something else and let me understand some of the detail of a problem that sits across the service. (And also get the chance to work closely with Lisa and content designer Izzy.)</p>

<p>I need to have a difficult conversation about another teamâ€™s involvement. As we are starting small with our upcoming beta, I need to keep the team focused on that, not get distracted by chats about â€œscalingâ€.</p>

<p>Keep reminding people â€œjust because thatâ€™s how we currently do things in DWP doesnâ€™t mean we have to keep doing it or do it againâ€. Focus on outcomes. If we can lean on the existing, great though.</p>

